    <h1>FAQ's</h1>

    	<div >
			<dl>
			    <dt><strong>Q. Who can I contact if I need help with the Tutorials?</strong></dt>
					<dd>A. On the contact page there is a contact us form, which you can complete and a lecturer from DBS will contact you. </dd>
				<dt><strong>How do I change my password? </strong></dt>
					<dd></dd>
				<dt><strong>Q. Who do I contact if I forget my password?</strong></dt>
					<dd>A. Your password is the same as your main DBS password, if you forget it, you will need to contact DBS’s IT Department. They will reset it for you.</dd>	
       			<dt><strong>Q. How long do I have to complete a course tutorial?</strong></dt>
					<dd>A. You have 90 days to complete the course tutorial.  If you have not completed the course at this time, you can contact DBS who will discuss your options with you. </dd>
				<dt><strong>Q. How many courses can I complete at one time?</strong></dt>
					<dd>A. You can take two courses at one time.</dd>
                <dt><strong>Q. How many times can I complete the mock exam on each course?</strong></dt>
                    <dd>A. There is no limit as to how many times you can take the mock exam.</dd>
                <dt><strong>Q. Who writes the content for Toodle?</strong></dt>
                    <dd>A. Lecturers in DBS write the content to all our courses on Toodle. </dd>
                <dt><strong>Q. Can I meet up with a lecturer if I am having difficulty with a course?</strong></dt>
                    <dd>A. Firstly we would ask you to fill in the contact form and a lecturer will be in contact with you.  If they feel that a meeting is necessary, they can organize it with you.</dd>
                <dt><strong>Q. Can I log in to Toodle from any computer?</strong></dt>
                    <dd>A. Yes you can, once you have access to a web browser you can access the  Toodle website and your course content. </dd>
                <dt><strong>Q. Why does the streaming movie keep pausing?</strong></dt>
                    <dd>A. You are probably experiencing problems with your network connection.  You can view movies over 3G, 4G or Wi-Fi, but we recommend watching them over Wi-Fi. </dd>

			</dl>
